            "title": "Malaysian Telcos May Need More Funding to Defend 5G Position — Market Talk",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-Xl9a4Ubk body-nzzZVyQ3 content-nzzZVyQ3\"><div><span><p class=\"\"><span>Additional funding from Malaysia telcos is necessary for Digital Nasional to remain competitive, particularly as U Mobile rolls out the country's second 5G network and intensifies competition, TA Securities analyst Chan Mun Chun says in a note. Digital Nasional is Malaysia's state-backed 5G infrastructure operator. Digital Nasional's 5G network now covers 82.4% of populated areas, while U Mobile has reached about 80%, narrowing the gap and pushing the market toward a dual-network model, he says. Chan expects Digital Nasional to keep investing in network upgrades and service quality to defend its lead. Despite rising competition, Malaysia's telecom sector revenue outlook remains resilient as operators are likely to focus on stronger service offerings rather than aggressive price cuts, while enterprise 5G adoption offers fresh growth opportunities, he adds. (yingxian.wong@wsj.com)</span></p></span></div></div>",
